  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_6' aria-label=\" Sanjay Prakash & Ors. versus Union of India & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('6','2025','2025_5_2726_2763','2025INSC779'); ><font size='4'> <strong>SANJAY PRAKASH & ORS.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>UNION OF INDIA & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 5 S.C.R. 2726</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 779</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010008442025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : ABHAY S. OKA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, UJJAL BHUYAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether the Central Armed Police Forces (CAPFs) are included in Organized Group-A Service (OGAS); all benefits available to OGAS, if available to the CAPFs. Headnotes&dagger; Central Armed Police Forces (CAPFs) &ndash; CRPF, BSF, SSB, ITBP and CISF, collectively known as Service (OGAS) &ndash; All benefits available to OGAS, if available to the CAPFs &ndash; Grievances of the appellants- officers belonging to different CAPFs were non-recognition as OGAS, non-grant of Non-Functional Financial Upgradation (NFFU) and service stagnation because of lateral entry by<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 23-05-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 13104/2024</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Disposed off</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('6','2025','2025_5_2726_2763','2025INSC779','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'